      "end": 13.28,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain. For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 14.1,
      "end": 22.16,
      "text": "Recorded by Lee Dunkleberg. Dunkleberg.com. D-U-N-K-E-L-B-E-R-G.com.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 23.22,
      "end": 26.96,
      "text": "ASOPS Fables. The Lion and the Wild-S.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 28.1,
      "end": 40.46,
      "text": "A Lion and a Wild-S went out hunting together. The latter was to run down the prey by his superior speed, and the former would then come up and dispatch it.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 41.12,
      "end": 49.38,
      "text": "They met with great success, and when it came to sharing the spoil, the Lion divided it all into three equal portions.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 49.38,
      "end": 66.44,
      "text": "I will take the first, said he, because I am King of the Beast. I will also take the second, because as your partner, I am entitled to half of what remains.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 67.98,
      "end": 81.96,
      "text": "And as for the third, well, unless you give it up to me, and take yourself off pretty quick, the third, believe me, will make you feel very sorry for yourself.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 83.26,
      "end": 88.08,
      "text": "Might makes right. End of the Lion and the Wild-S.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
